        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 24 at 7:16PM CDT until July 24 at 7:45PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 715 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles north of
Canadian, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southwestern Lipscomb, northwestern Hemphill and eastern Ochiltree
Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
